articles.title: About
articles.contents:
I’m currently a doctoral student in the Department of Educational
Measurement & Statistics at the University of Iowa. I basically use this
site to show my recent, current, and future works as well as some
tutorials about R programming in a way that tries to make my efforts
more interactive.
My research interests are mostly focused on the development of
psychometric and general quantitative methods, as applied in the
psychological, educational, and social sciences. I’m now the Graduate
Teaching Assistant of Multivariate Statistics.
My Website: jihongzhang.org
My Email: jihong-zhang@uiowa.edu
